The public API relies on CmdLineParser, which is fine, but I might need to add some imports like java.util.HashMap. I’m thinking about reducing tests to four to focus on one-to-one calls for FieldSetter. I need to ensure type annotations in functions and variables are clear and explicit, keeping the overall structure in mind.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing FieldSetter test setup**\\n\\nI’m looking at the PublicOptionBean, which is a public static class nested within the public FieldSetterTest. Its public field is indeed accessible. I’m wondering if the Reflection Field#set method from org.kohsuke.args4j.spi can access this public member. The nested public static class should work, but I have a private option string that’s causing issues on line 39 when f.set fails. It seems I need to check the MapOptionHandler parse method that adds values correctly but returns null at a specific point.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_WXigiyMfkpNoBu1Dpx8Vqcqw|fc_078490df7ba8417f0169f517c77564819593495e6cb2899297", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/args4j/args4j/2.0.26/src/test/java/args4j/args4j/FieldSetterTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage args4j.args4j;\n\nimport java.util.HashMap;\nimport java.util.Map;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.kohsuke.args4j.CmdLineException;\nimport org.kohsuke.args4j.CmdLineParser;\nimport org.kohsuke.args4j.Option;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class FieldSetterTest {\n    @Test\n    void parsesOptionIntoPublicField() throws CmdLineException {\n        PublicOptionBean bean = new PublicOptionBean();\n        CmdLineParser parser = new CmdLineParser(bean);\n\n        parser.parseArgument(\"-name\", \"public-value\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.name).isEqualTo(\"public-value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void parsesOptionIntoPrivateField() throws CmdLineException {\n        PrivateOptionBean bean = new PrivateOptionBean();\n        CmdLineParser parser = new CmdLineParser(bean);\n\n        parser.parseArgument(\"-name\", \"private-value\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.name()).isEqualTo(\"private-value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void parsesMapOptionIntoPublicField() throws CmdLineException {\n        PublicMapOptionBean bean = new PublicMapOptionBean();\n        CmdLineParser parser = new CmdLineParser(bean);\n\n        parser.parseArgument(\"-property\", \"alpha=one\", \"-property\", \"beta=two\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.properties)\n                .containsEntry(\"alpha\", \"one\")\n                .containsEntry(\"beta\", \"two\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void parsesMapOptionIntoExistingPrivateField() throws CmdLineException {\n        PrivateMapOptionBean bean = new PrivateMapOptionBean();\n        CmdLineParser parser = new CmdLineParser(bean);\n\n        parser.parseArgument(\"-property\", \"alpha=one\");\n\n        assertThat(bean.properties()).containsEntry(\"alpha\", \"one\");\n    }\n\n    public static class PublicOptionBean {\n        @Option(name = \"-name\")\n        public String name;\n    }\n\n    public static class PrivateOptionBean {\n        @Option(name = \"-name\")\n        private String name;\n\n        String name() {\n            return name;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class PublicMapOptionBean {\n        @Option(name = \"-property\")\n        public Map<String, String> properties;\n    }\n\n    public static class PrivateMapOptionBean {\n        @Option(name = \"-property\")\n        private Map<String, String> properties = new HashMap<String, String>();\n\n        Map<String, String> properties() {\n            return properties;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 533, "output": 1497, "c